This is the Vlerq 1.7 source code area.


Build instructions for LuaVlerq as loadable extension for Lua:
    # edit src/config as appropriate, the default is set up for Mac OS X
    cd src
    make
    make test       # <-- optional
    make install    # <-- optional
The tests use the "shake" tool [http://luaforge.net/projects/shake], but
they can also be run using "lua test.lua" (assuming "lua" is installed).


Alternate manual build of LuaVlerq:
    cd src
  Windows with Mingw, this requires the Lua dll:
    gcc -Os -I../lua/src -shared -Wl,-s -o vq.dll vq.c ../lua/src/lua51.dll
  Linux:
    gcc -Os -I../lua/src -shared -Wl,-s -fPIC -o vq.so vq.c
  Mac OS X:
    gcc -Os -I../lua/src -bundle -undefined dynamic_lookup -Wl,-x -o vq.so vq.c


Build instructions for Vqx, a standalone executable with Lua built-in:
    cd vqx
    make
    make test

    
The complete source code of Lua is included in the "lua" subdirectory.
Vlerq is Open Source Software, see src/vlerq.h (MIT-license, same as Lua).

The http://vlerq.org/ website has the latest news and documentation.
